description: From Latin latibulum (“hiding place”), from latere (“to lie hid”) + -ize.

verbs.description: latibulize (third-person singular simple present latibulizes, present participle latibulizing, simple past and past participle latibulized)

entries.meaning: (rare, archaic, intransitive) To retire into a den, or hole, and lie dormant in winter.
examples: When kept in gardens in Italy and Germany, it is observed to latibulize in October, and to reappear in April.
